i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Raimbaud II d’Orange was born in 1066, in Orange, Vaucluse, France, his father, Bertrand Count Of Orange, was 1 and his mother, Alice Countess Of Orange, was -1. He had at least 2 daughters with Arcelene de Francon. He died about 1122, in Israel, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1066–About 1122":"1066–umbes 1122","1066–1122":"1066–1122","1055–Female":"1055–Surnud","1096–1136":"1096–1136","1120–1173":"1120–1173","1066–Male":"1066–Surnud","1068–Female":"1068–Surnud","avant 1096":"enne 1096","Abt 1120":"umbes 1120","1136":"1136","1068":"1068","1122":"1122","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1120":"1120","1173":"1173","1096":"1096","About 1122":"umbes 1122","Orange, Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte D'azur, France":"Orange, Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, Prantsusmaa","Israël":"Iisrael","Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France":"Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, Prantsusmaa","Orange, Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, France":"Orange, Vaucluse, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1066–About 1122":"1066–noin 1122","1066–1122":"1066–1122","1055–Female":"1055–Kuollut","1096–1136":"1096–1136","1120–1173":"1120–1173","1066–Male":"1066–Kuollut","1068–Female":"1068–Kuollut","avant 1096":"ennen vuotta 1096","Abt 1120":"noin 1120","1136":"1136","1068":"1068","1122":"1122","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1120":"1120","1173":"1173","1096":"1096","About 1122":"noin 1122","Orange, Vaucluse, Provence-Alpes-Côte D'azur, Fr